            __builder.AddMarkupContent(0, "<div style=\"max-width: 650px; margin: auto; margin-top: 80px;\">\r\n\r\n        <h1>RPG Design Document</h1>\r\n        <p>\r\n            This RPG game is text-based (supported by minor graphics) RPG game which is played in the browser. \r\n            The goal of the game is to advance the character with experience, better items, and equipment.\r\n        </p>\r\n        <p>\r\n            The game is single-player, and is player in the browser. Should this be multiplayer?\r\n        </p>\r\n\r\n        <section>\r\n            <h2>Character</h2>\r\n            <p>\r\n                A character is defined by his/her attributes and equipment. The combination\r\n                of these two will determine how combate evolves.\r\n            </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n                The characters in the game are highly customizable in the following areas:\r\n            </p>\r\n            <ul>\r\n                <li>Different kind of races</li>\r\n                <li>Both genders: male/female</li>\r\n                <li>All weapons and armor are shown</li>\r\n            </ul>\r\n            <p>Some races also have different skin tones available.</p>\r\n\r\n            <h3>Races</h3>\r\n            <p>\r\n                At the beginning of the game, there are four different available races.\r\n                There are more 2D models available for other races.\r\n            </p>\r\n            <table>\r\n                <thead>\r\n                    <tr>\r\n                        <td>Race</td>\r\n                        <td>2D Model</td>\r\n                        <td>Racial bonus</td>\r\n                    </tr>\r\n                </thead>\r\n                <tbody>\r\n                    <tr>\r\n                        <td>Human</td>\r\n                        <td>\r\n                            <div class=\"tile tile-1118\"></div>\r\n                            <div class=\"tile tile-1119\"></div>\r\n                        </td>\r\n                        <td>Earn 10% more gold from combat, and chests.</td>\r\n                    </tr>\r\n                    <tr>\r\n                        <td>Elf</td>\r\n                        <td>\r\n                            <div class=\"tile tile-1138\"></div>\r\n                            <div class=\"tile tile-1139\"></div>\r\n                        </td>\r\n                        <td>Intelligence is increased by 4.</td>\r\n                    </tr>\r\n                    <tr>\r\n                        <td>Orc</td>\r\n                        <td>\r\n                            <div class=\"tile tile-1113\"></div>\r\n                            <div class=\"tile tile-1114\"></div>\r\n                        </td>\r\n                        <td>Strength is increased by 4.</td>\r\n                    </tr>\r\n                    <tr>\r\n                        <td>Draconian</td>\r\n                        <td>\r\n                            <div class=\"tile tile-1115\"></div>\r\n                            <div class=\"tile tile-1116\"></div>\r\n                        </td>\r\n                        <td>Dexterity is increased by 4.</td>\r\n                    </tr>\r\n                </tbody>\r\n            </table>\r\n            <p>Which gender? Which race? Classes? Attributes?</p>\r\n\r\n            <h3>Attributes</h3>\r\n            <p>\r\n                A character is defined by the following attributes:\r\n            </p>\r\n            <table>\r\n                <thead>\r\n                    <tr>\r\n                        <td>Attribute</td>\r\n                        <td>Description</td>\r\n                    </tr>\r\n                </thead>\r\n                <tbody>\r\n                    <tr>\r\n                        <td>Strength</td>\r\n                        <td>Determines how much damage is dealt, and inventory capacity.</td>\r\n                    </tr>\r\n                    <tr>\r\n                        <td>Dexterity</td>\r\n                        <td>Determines how likely a crit is to occur.</td>\r\n                    </tr>\r\n                    <tr>\r\n                        <td>Constitution</td>\r\n                        <td>Determines the number of hitpoints.</td>\r\n                    </tr>\r\n                    <tr>\r\n                        <td>Intelligence</td>\r\n                        <td>Determines how much magic damage is dealt.</td>\r\n                    </tr>\r\n                    <tr>\r\n                        <td>Wisdom</td>\r\n                        <td>Determines how much mana the player has.</td>\r\n                    </tr>\r\n                    <tr>\r\n                        <td>Memory</td>\r\n                        <td>Determines how many skills, and knowledge a player can learn.</td>\r\n                    </tr>\r\n                </tbody>\r\n            </table>\r\n\r\n            <h3>Classes</h3>\r\n            <p>\r\n                The game does not have any classes. A player is also allowed to learn every possible skills.\r\n                Weapons give damage or magic damage, which is increased by strength/intelligence. \r\n            </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n                This will lead to interesting characters, but also the ability to break a character.\r\n                It should be possible to rebalance the attributes.\r\n            </p>\r\n\r\n        </section>\r\n\r\n        <section>\r\n            <h2>Civil</h2>\r\n            <p>\r\n                Civil attributes allow for various other activities for a player. \r\n                Most of these activities will help a player to earn gold.\r\n            </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n                A player will get 1 civil point for each two levels. \r\n                The maximum level for a civil attribute is level 5.\r\n            </p>\r\n            <table>\r\n                <thead>\r\n                    <tr>\r\n                        <td>Civil</td>\r\n                        <td>Description</td>\r\n                    </tr>\r\n                </thead>\r\n                <tbody>\r\n                    <tr>\r\n                        <td>Bartering</td>\r\n                        <td>Better shop prices for buying and selling.</td>\r\n                    </tr>\r\n                    <tr>\r\n                        <td>Loremaster</td>\r\n                        <td>Identify high level items and see monster information.</td>\r\n                    </tr>\r\n                    <tr>\r\n                        <td>Thieving</td>\r\n                        <td>Pickpocket from NPCs.</td>\r\n                    </tr>\r\n                    <tr>\r\n                        <td>Luck</td>\r\n                        <td>Better loot from chests.</td>\r\n                    </tr>\r\n                </tbody>\r\n            </table>\r\n        </section>\r\n\r\n        <section>\r\n            <h2>Inventory</h2>\r\n            <p>\r\n                The inventory holds all the players\' items. The inventory allows for\r\n                the following actions: use, equip, discard, etc.\r\n            </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n                A player will be able to carry a certain amount of different items based on\r\n                the players\' strength.\r\n            </p>\r\n        </section>\r\n\r\n        <section>\r\n            <h2>Items</h2>\r\n            <p>Which kind of items are there? How is value determined? How are items obtained? How are items sold?</p>\r\n            <table>\r\n                <thead>\r\n                    <tr>\r\n                        <td>Item</td>\r\n                        <td>Description</td>\r\n                        <td>2D Model</td>\r\n                    </tr>\r\n                </thead>\r\n                <tbody>\r\n                    <tr>\r\n                        <td>Gold</td>\r\n                        <td>Used as game currency.</td>\r\n                        <td><div class=\"tile tile-1605\"></div></td>\r\n                    </tr>\r\n                </tbody>\r\n            </table>\r\n        </section>\r\n\r\n        <section>\r\n            <h2>Equipment</h2>\r\n            <p>Which types of equipment are there? How strong is the equipment? How is damage/defense determined? How is equipment enchanted?</p>\r\n\r\n        </section>\r\n\r\n        <section>\r\n            <h2>Skills</h2>\r\n            <p>Which skills are there? Is the skill a combat skill, magic skill, or a buff?</p>\r\n            <p>\r\n                A skill will do combat or magic damage. This damage is increased by the attributes and equipment.\r\n                This means that if a player is built for combat damage, and uses a magic damage weapon, then this will\r\n                be sub-par to a player that is build for magic damage.\r\n            </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n                A skill has a certain amount of turn cooldown. During this time the skill cannot be used.\r\n            </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n                A magic skill will consume mana. It is important for magic based characters to\r\n                bring mana potions with them.\r\n            </p>\r\n            <h3>Combat skills</h3>\r\n            There are the following combat skills:\r\n\r\n            <h3>Magic skills</h3>\r\n            There are the following magic skills:\r\n        </section>\r\n\r\n        <section>\r\n            <h2>Effects</h2>\r\n            <p>How does the effect (buff) system work?</p>\r\n        </section>\r\n\r\n        <section>\r\n            <h2>Log</h2>\r\n            <p>What is the log output? Which kinds of log output are there?</p>\r\n        </section>\r\n\r\n        <section>\r\n            <h2>Map</h2>\r\n            <p>How does the map work? Map objects vs. world objects.</p>\r\n        </section>\r\n\r\n        <section>\r\n            <h2>NPCs</h2>\r\n            <p>What are NPC\'s? How can you interact with NPCs? How does the dialog system work?</p>\r\n        </section>\r\n\r\n        <section>\r\n            <h2>Enemies</h2>\r\n            <p>Which enemies are there? How strong are they?</p>\r\n        </section>\r\n\r\n        <section>\r\n            <h2>Combat</h2>\r\n            <p>How does the combat system work? How do dungeons work?</p>\r\n        </section>\r\n\r\n        <section>\r\n            <h2>Crafting</h2>\r\n            <p>How does the crafting system work? How are recipes acquired? How is equipment crafted? Which skills are required? How to obtain materials?</p>\r\n        </section>\r\n\r\n        <section>\r\n            <h2>Quests</h2>\r\n            <p>How does the quest system work?</p>\r\n        </section>\r\n\r\n        <section>\r\n            <h2>Shops</h2>\r\n            <p>Which items are sold? How does one interact with a shop?</p>\r\n        </section>\r\n\r\n        <section>\r\n            <h2>Learning</h2>\r\n            <p>How does a player learn new skills? How does the learning system work?</p>\r\n        </section>\r\n\r\n    </div>");
